Build succeeds. Here's the summary:

### What changed

**`ReportGenerator.cs`** now takes `IFileSystem` via primary constructor and calls `fileSystem.File.*`, `fileSystem.Directory.*`, and `fileSystem.Path.*` instead of the static `File`/`Directory`/`Path` classes.

### DI registration (in `Program.cs` / `Startup.cs`)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

### Testing with `MockFileSystem`

Install the test helpers in your test project:
```
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

Then mock everything in-memory:
```csharp
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem();
mockFs.Directory.CreateDirectory("/tmp/reports");
var generator = new ReportGenerator(mockFs);

var path = generator.GenerateReport("sales");

Assert.True(mockFs.File.Exists(path));
Assert.Contains("Report: sales", mockFs.File.ReadAllText(path));
```

No real files touched, fully deterministic, and parallel-test safe. Note that `DateTime.UtcNow` and `Environment.*` are also statics in this class — if you want to make those testable too, consider `TimeProvider` (built-in on .NET 8+) and a custom `IEnvironmentProvider` wrapper.
